{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Now, since this is TEDGlobal,"},{"time":2000,"text":"who can tell me what this is called in French?"},{"time":6000,"text":"I see you're all up on the history of hurdy-gurdy --"},{"time":8000,"text":"\"vielle Ã  roue.\""},{"time":10000,"text":"And in Spanish, \"zanfona.\""},{"time":12000,"text":"And in Italian, \"ghironda,\" okay?"},{"time":14000,"text":"Hurdy-gurdy, or wheel fiddle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17000,"text":"So, these are the different kinds and shapes of the hurdy-gurdy."},{"time":20000,"text":"The hurdy-gurdy is the only musical instrument"},{"time":23000,"text":"that uses a crank to turn a wheel"},{"time":26000,"text":"to rub strings, like the bow of a violin,"},{"time":29000,"text":"to produce music."},{"time":31000,"text":"It has three different kinds of strings."},{"time":34000,"text":"The first string is the drone string,"},{"time":37000,"text":"which plays a continuous sound like the bagpipe."},{"time":42000,"text":"The second string is a melody string,"},{"time":44000,"text":"which is played with a wooden keyboard tuned like a piano."},{"time":53000,"text":"And the third string is pretty innovative."},{"time":55000,"text":"It's also the only instrument"},{"time":57000,"text":"that uses this kind of technique."},{"time":60000,"text":"It activates what's called the buzzing bridge, or the dog."},{"time":64000,"text":"When I turn the crank and I apply pressure,"},{"time":70000,"text":"it makes a sound like a barking dog."},{"time":74000,"text":"So all of this is pretty innovative,"},{"time":76000,"text":"if you consider"},{"time":78000,"text":"that the hurdy-gurdy appeared about a thousand years ago"},{"time":80000,"text":"and it took two people to play it;"},{"time":82000,"text":"one to turn the crank,"},{"time":84000,"text":"and another person -- yes -- to play the melody"},{"time":86000,"text":"by physically pulling up large wooden pegs."},{"time":90000,"text":"Luckily, all of this changed a couple of centuries later."},{"time":93000,"text":"So, one person could actually play"},{"time":95000,"text":"and almost -- this is pretty heavy --"},{"time":97000,"text":"carry the hurdy-gurdy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100000,"text":"The hurdy-gurdy has been used, historically, through the centuries"},{"time":103000,"text":"in mostly dance music"},{"time":105000,"text":"because of the uniqueness of the melody"},{"time":108000,"text":"combined with the acoustic boombox here."},{"time":111000,"text":"And today, the hurdy-gurdy is used in all sorts of music --"},{"time":114000,"text":"traditional folk music,"},{"time":116000,"text":"dance, contemporary"},{"time":118000,"text":"and world music --"},{"time":121000,"text":"in the U.K., in France, in Spain"},{"time":123000,"text":"and in Italy."},{"time":125000,"text":"And this kind of hurdy-gurdy takes anywhere from three to five years [to order and receive it]."},{"time":128000,"text":"It's made by specialized luthiers,"},{"time":130000,"text":"also in Europe."},{"time":133000,"text":"And it's very difficult to tune."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137000,"text":"So without further ado, would you like to hear it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"(Audience: Yes.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"Caroline Phillips: I didn't hear you. Would you like to hear it? (Audience: Yes!)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":143000,"text":"CP: Okay."},{"time":145000,"text":"There I go."},{"time":148000,"text":"I'd like to sing in Basque,"},{"time":150000,"text":"which is the language spoken in the Basque Country where I live,"},{"time":153000,"text":"in the region in France and Spain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165000,"text":"[Basque]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":261000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265000,"text":"This is a song that I wrote"},{"time":268000,"text":"based on traditional Basque rhythms."},{"time":271000,"text":"And this is a song that has a kind of a Celtic feel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":315000,"text":"Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}